y of the Android accessibility tree for debugging."}, "description": {"en-US": "Tree Viewer is a developer tool that uses Android's AccessibilityService to display the UI tree of the current screen as a live overlay.\n\nFeatures:\n- Left-half overlay showing the full accessibility tree with indentation\n- Tags for clickable, editable, scrollable, and long-clickable elements\n- Text content and content descriptions displayed inline\n- Right-half overlay with interactive blocks for clickable elements\n- Blocks show color-coded action availability (click/long-click)\n- Page up/down navigation for the log view\n- Show/hide toggle for the right-side overlay\n- Pass-through touch on the log overlay (taps reach the app underneath)\n- Auto-refreshes on screen content changes with debounce\n\nPermissions:\n- Draw over other apps (SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW) — for the overlay display\n- Accessibility Service — to read the UI tree\n\nThis app is intended for developers and accessibility testers. It does not collect, store, or transmit any data.\n"}, "preferredSigner": "bbd288b142ad088c34c184ea99f5b522306782759fc2d6074913e5a2b92d914c"}, "versions": {"c72d3616f0e9ec510fa37dc1d1d67d1cfe2232162e9df311ef205c07b28bf347": {"added": 1774178996000, "file": {"name": "/com.prado.treeviewer-v73.apk", "sha256": "c72d3616f0e9ec510fa37dc1d1d67d1cfe2232162e9df311ef205c07b28bf347", "size": 64668642}, "manifest": {"nativecode": ["arm64-v8a"], "versionName": "1.073", "versionCode": 73, "usesSdk": {"minSdkVersion": 26, "targetSdkVersion": 33}, "signer": {"sha256": ["bbd288b142ad088c34c184ea99f5b522306782759fc2d6074913e5a2b92d914c"]}, "usesPermission": [{"name": "android.permission.SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW"}, {"name": "android.permission.INTERNET"}, {"name": "android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO"}, {"name": "android.permission.MODIFY_AUDIO_SETTINGS"}, {"name": "android.permission.MEDIA_CONTENT_CONTROL"}, {"name": "android.permission.MODIFY_AUDIO_ROUTING"}, {"name": "android.permission.QUERY_AUDIO_STATE"}, {"name":